Kobold's Neighbor					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait															PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Kobold's Neighbor],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:You grew up in wilderness where kobolds make their homes. You learned early on how to find traps before they find you, how to disable them, and when you should just walk away. You gain a +2 trait bonus to Perception checks to discover traps and a +1 trait bonus to Disable Device checks.						BONUS:SITUATION|Perception=Trapfinding|2|TYPE=Trait	BONUS:SKILL|Disable Device|1|TYPE=Trait							SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Bellis Axe Master		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.AttackOption		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Bellis)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bellis Axe Master],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					DESC:No one knows how to swing an axe better than a Bellisian! You gain a +2 trait bonus on all rolls made to confirm critical hits with axes (battle axe, hand axe, or greataxe).																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Bellis Honey Harvester	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.SaveBonus.Defensive	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Bellis)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bellis Honey Harvester],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]				DESC:Your frequent exposure to bees-and their stings-makes all such creatures seem more like nuisances than actual threats. You gain DR 3/- against damage dealt by swarms and a +1 trait bonus on saving throws against distraction and poison from swarms.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.18	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+1 vs. distraction and poison from swarms
Bellis Log Roller		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Bellis)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Bellis Log Roller],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					DESC:The time you spent leaping between slippery logs as they whirled down the Sellen River taught you how to keep your footing. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Acrobatics checks and a +1 trait bonus to your CMB when attempting to resist trip attacks.																						BONUS:SKILL|Acrobatics|1|TYPE=Trait		BONUS:VAR|CMD_Trip|1|TYPE=Trait	SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Carpenden Lobber		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.AttackOption		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Carpenden)	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Carpenden Lobber],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					DESC:Your regular participation in the moonmelon festival has made you wickedly effective at hurling harmless objects. You gain a +2 trait bonus on attack rolls when throwing items that do not deal normal hit point damage (such as weapons that deal nonlethal damage or items such as tanglefoot bags and thunderstones).																							SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Carpenden Roof Runner	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Carpenden)	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Carpenden Roof Runner],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					DESC:Your childhood playing atop Carpenden's buildings has given you a remarkable head for heights. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Acrobatics checks made when you are at least 20 feet above the ground.																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Oregent Desperation	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Oregent)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Desperation],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]					DESC:Your instinct to survive easily overpowers your intellect, and you consider this a more-than-fair trade. Once per day you can improve your condition from dying to disabled by taking 4 points of Intelligence damage.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Oregent Timing		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Oregent)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Timing],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]						DESC:After years of soul-numbing obedience to the schedules of others, you find synchronizing your actions with an ally second nature. Once per day when you take a readied action in combat, you gain a +3 trait bonus on the d20 roll for that action if it was triggered by an ally's action.																												SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Oregent Vandal		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait.AttackOption		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Background,Andoran (City of Oregent)		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Vandal],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]						DESC:You find it quite easy to apply your carefully honed instincts for building and repairing to destruction instead. You gain a +2 trait bonus on damage rolls made against targets with hardness. This bonus does not apply to attacks that ignore hardness.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.20

